The Motley Fool












Wall Street is getting it all wrong... And we believe the little guy can outsmart the market with a simple investing strategy
Our time-tested investing approach has resulted in market-beating returns. In fact, The Motley Fool's newsletter services earned the top three spots in Wall Street Journal columnist Mark Hulbert's August 2013 ranking of more than 200 services he tracks.





The Motley Fool's Secret to Uncovering Wealth-Building Buys




Buy Businesses, Not TickersStraight from the mouth of famed investor Peter Lynch, we buy into a company's prospects, future, and management, and we put our money into companies that will generate shareholder value over the long term.


Be a Lifetime InvestorWe're investors that believe the best way to beat the market is to hold stocks for the long term. But we don't just buy and forget about our stocks. We dive deep into research, keep a close eye on our investing thesis, and relentlessly pursue compelling stocks we think will outperform.




Fish Where Others Aren'tWe're not interested in following the crowds or what Wall Street thinks is the next hot stock. That's a money-losing strategy! We are interested in thinking for ourselves and scoring profits with unbiased research.


Be Foolish and Have FunMany believe the little guy can't win in the market, but we believe our members can beat Wall Street professionals... and we think you should have fun along the way.





Tom Gardner - (TMFTomG)
Tom co-founded The Motley Fool with his brother David in 1992. He now serves as its CEO and Chairman. Glassdoor ranked The Motley Fool as the top small- to medium-size company to work for in the U.S. two years in a row. Tom serves as the lead advisor on Motley Fool One - the Fool's all-access service. He also co-manages Stock Advisor, a service that can boast that since 2002, the average stock pick is up 265%... that's doubling the performance of the S&P 500.

David Gardner - (TMFSpiffyPop)
Motley Fool Co-Founder David Gardner is recognized as one of the top growth investors in America. He has picked numerous multi-baggers, including AOL, Starbucks, Amazon, and Netflix in the early days. David is the lead advisor for Motley Fool Rule Breakers - the Fool's service for finding disruptive companies to score massive profits. David also Co-manages Stock Advisor along with Tom.

 
