Boussard & Gavaudan Investment Management LLP Buys 566,447 Shares of Constellium N.V. (CSTM)


					Posted by Harper Lund on Jul 18th, 2017 // No Comments




Boussard & Gavaudan Investment Management LLP increased its position in shares of  Constellium N.V. (NYSE:CSTM) by 59.8% during the second quarter, according to its most recent disclosure with the SEC. The fund owned 1,513,802 shares of the industrial products company’s stock after buying an additional 566,447 shares during the period. Constellium N.V. accounts for approximately  0.7% of Boussard & Gavaudan Investment Management LLP’s investment portfolio, making the stock its 7th largest position. Boussard & Gavaudan Investment Management LLP owned about 1.40% of Constellium N.V. worth $10,332,000 at the end of the most recent reporting period. 
Other large investors also recently made changes to their positions in the company. Vaughan Nelson Investment Management L.P. increased its position in shares of  Constellium N.V. by 0.8% in the second quarter. Vaughan Nelson Investment Management L.P. now owns 5,696,175 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $39,303,000 after buying an additional 44,200 shares in the last quarter.  Jennison Associates LLC increased its stake in shares of  Constellium N.V. by 2.9% in the first quarter. Jennison Associates LLC now owns 3,999,318 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $25,996,000 after buying an additional 111,649 shares in the last quarter.  Canyon Capital Advisors LLC bought a new stake in shares of  Constellium N.V. during the first quarter valued at $19,706,000.  Bronson Point Management LLC increased its stake in shares of  Constellium N.V. by 25.6% in the first quarter. Bronson Point Management LLC now owns 2,343,222 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $15,231,000 after buying an additional 478,222 shares in the last quarter.  Finally, Sound Point Capital Management LP increased its stake in shares of  Constellium N.V. by 32.5% in the first quarter. Sound Point Capital Management LP now owns 2,065,495 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $13,426,000 after buying an additional 506,945 shares in the last quarter. Institutional investors and hedge funds own  60.00% of the company’s stock. 


 Get Constellium N.V. alerts:



Constellium N.V. (NYSE:CSTM) traded down 1.21% during trading on Tuesday, hitting $8.15. 297,320 shares of the stock were exchanged. Constellium N.V. has a one year low of $4.79 and a one year high of $8.85. The company has a market cap of $882.91 million, a price-to-earnings ratio of 45.03 and a beta of 0.71. The stock’s 50 day moving average is $6.75 and its 200-day moving average is $6.75. 





Constellium N.V. (NYSE:CSTM) last released its earnings results on Thursday, April 27th. The industrial products company reported $0.13 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, topping analysts’ consensus estimates of $0.09 by $0.04. The firm had revenue of $1.33 billion for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $1.34 billion. Constellium N.V. had a negative return on equity of 2.96% and a net margin of 0.35%. Constellium N.V.’s revenue was up 15.5% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same period in the previous year, the company earned ($0.08) earnings per share.  On average, equities research analysts expect that  Constellium N.V. will post $0.77 earnings per share for the current fiscal year. 
