Motley Fool Wealth Management LLC Cuts Stake in Illinois Tool Works Inc. (ITW)

					Posted by Sally Masters on Jul 24th, 2017 // No Comments 



Motley Fool Wealth Management LLC lowered its position in  Illinois Tool Works Inc. (NYSE:ITW) by 4.9% during the first quarter, according to its most recent disclosure with the SEC. The firm owned 14,805 shares of the industrial products company’s stock after selling 759 shares during the period. Motley Fool Wealth Management LLC’s holdings in Illinois Tool Works were worth $1,961,000 at the end of the most recent reporting period. 
A number of other hedge funds have also modified their holdings of the company. Kentucky Retirement Systems acquired a new stake in shares of  Illinois Tool Works during the fourth quarter worth $2,807,000.  Bremer Trust National Association boosted its stake in shares of  Illinois Tool Works by 1.7% in the first quarter. Bremer Trust National Association now owns 23,697 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $3,139,000 after buying an additional 402 shares during the last quarter.  Elkhorn Investments LLC acquired a new stake in shares of  Illinois Tool Works during the first quarter worth $1,284,000.  HighPoint Advisor Group LLC boosted its stake in shares of  Illinois Tool Works by 0.4% in the fourth quarter. HighPoint Advisor Group LLC now owns 8,947 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $1,207,000 after buying an additional 33 shares during the last quarter.  Finally, Mn Services Vermogensbeheer B.V. boosted its stake in shares of  Illinois Tool Works by 1.1% in the first quarter. Mn Services Vermogensbeheer B.V. now owns 8,425 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $1,043,000 after buying an additional 91 shares during the last quarter. Hedge funds and other institutional investors own  75.51% of the company’s stock. 


 Get Illinois Tool Works Inc. alerts:



Illinois Tool Works Inc. (NYSE ITW) opened at 147.29 on Monday. The firm has a market cap of $50.88 billion, a price-to-earnings ratio of 24.74 and a beta of 1.12. Illinois Tool Works Inc. has a 1-year low of $111.50 and a 1-year high of $150.29. The company has a 50-day moving average of $145.53 and a 200-day moving average of $135.52. 




Illinois Tool Works (NYSE:ITW) last issued its earnings results on Monday, April 24th. The industrial products company reported $1.54 EPS for the quarter, beating the Thomson Reuters’ consensus estimate of $1.45 by $0.09. Illinois Tool Works had a net margin of 15.24% and a return on equity of 45.02%. The firm had revenue of $3.47 billion during the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $3.40 billion. During the same quarter in the prior year, the firm earned $1.29 earnings per share. The business’s quarterly revenue was up 6.0% on a year-over-year basis.  Analysts predict that  Illinois Tool Works Inc. will post $6.38 earnings per share for the current year. 
The company also recently announced a quarterly dividend, which was paid on Wednesday, July 12th. Shareholders of record on Friday, June 30th were paid a $0.65 dividend. This represents a $2.60 annualized dividend and a yield of 1.77%. The ex-dividend date  was Wednesday, June 28th. Illinois Tool Works’s payout ratio is presently 43.70%. 
