						Dorman Products, Inc. (DORM) Position Raised by Dubuque Bank & Trust Co.					

						 July 23rd, 2017  - 0 comments - Filed Under -
 by Latisha Jones 


							Filed Under: Finance - SEC Filing Articles 







Tweet










Dubuque Bank & Trust Co. raised its stake in shares of  Dorman Products, Inc. (NASDAQ:DORM) by 6.2% during the second quarter, according to its most recent 13F filing with the SEC. The fund owned 3,703 shares of the auto parts company’s stock after buying an additional 217 shares during the period. Dubuque Bank & Trust Co.’s holdings in Dorman Products were worth $306,000 at the end of the most recent reporting period. 
Several other large investors have also added to or reduced their stakes in DORM. BlackRock Inc. boosted its stake in  Dorman Products by 161,230.6% in the first quarter. BlackRock Inc. now owns 3,499,260 shares of the auto parts company’s stock valued at $287,394,000 after buying an additional 3,497,091 shares during the period.  FMR LLC acquired a new stake in  Dorman Products during the first quarter valued at approximately $29,140,000.  Norges Bank acquired a new stake in  Dorman Products during the fourth quarter valued at approximately $14,761,000.  Bank of New York Mellon Corp boosted its stake in  Dorman Products by 32.9% in the first quarter. Bank of New York Mellon Corp now owns 542,854 shares of the auto parts company’s stock valued at $44,585,000 after buying an additional 134,472 shares during the period.  Finally, Vanguard Group Inc. boosted its stake in  Dorman Products by 4.8% in the first quarter. Vanguard Group Inc. now owns 2,806,822 shares of the auto parts company’s stock valued at $230,525,000 after buying an additional 127,653 shares during the period. 77.12% of the stock is currently owned by institutional investors. 
Shares of Dorman Products, Inc. (NASDAQ:DORM) traded down 0.74% on Friday, reaching $76.94. The company’s stock had a trading volume of 145,125 shares. The firm has a 50 day moving average price of $79.93 and a 200-day moving average price of $77.87. Dorman Products, Inc. has a 12-month low of $56.10 and a 12-month high of $88.50. The stock has a market cap of $2.64 billion, a PE ratio of 23.97 and a beta of 0.63. 




Dorman Products (NASDAQ:DORM) last announced its quarterly earnings data on Tuesday, May 2nd. The auto parts company reported $0.85 earnings per share for the quarter, beating analysts’ consensus estimates of $0.79 by $0.06. The business had revenue of $221.60 million for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $224.16 million. Dorman Products had a return on equity of 18.79% and a net margin of 12.66%. The company’s revenue was up 6.4% on a year-over-year basis. During the same period in the prior year, the company earned $0.71 earnings per share.  Equities research analysts expect that  Dorman Products, Inc. will post $3.47 EPS for the current year. 
