In other news, Director Paul R. Lederer sold 7,593 shares of the stock in a transaction dated Friday, May 5th. The stock was sold at an average price of $82.70, for a total value of $627,941.10. Following the transaction, the director now directly owns 15,873 shares of the company’s stock, valued at $1,312,697.10. The sale was disclosed in a filing with the Securities & Exchange Commission, which can be accessed through the SEC website. 11.70% of the stock is currently owned by corporate insiders. 
About Dorman Products
Dorman Products, Inc is a supplier of replacement parts and fasteners for passenger cars, light trucks and heavy duty trucks in the automotive aftermarket. As of December 31, 2016, the Company distributed and marketed approximately 155,000 different stock keeping units (SKU’s) of automotive replacement parts and fasteners.
